snippet.textDisplay:
DNW (Did Not Watch, because the premise is absurd.)
The formation of axions requires the extremely hypothetical concept of C-Symmetry, the inversion of charges. Demonstrably, this does not happen. If it did, then the anti-matter, matter with inverted charges, formed from this inversion process and surrounded by, if not bound to, other matter would cause an immediate discharge of the anti-matter and an equal proportion of matter. BOOM! That's all there would be. BOOM! Axions do not exist because they cannot exist.

You get Theta as zero because physics on Earth is flawed. I don't mean practicing physics on Earth. I mean Earth science is flawed. For instance, when Quantum computers are being researched, it takes a few kilo amps and low temperatures to get any sort of reactance/Theta higher than zero going. And seriously, I don't mean an instance of that. I mean continuous to a point of which you get control of the field by either restarting the field or having it shut OFF when you make it happen. Also, the con of all that is "... it takes a few kilo amps and low temperatures to get any sort of reactance/Theta higher than zero going.". Again; That is because "...Earth science is flawed." as physics or other forms of ignored physics are practiced.

Also, I feel this sort of thing is simply renaming things that already exist. It's called Omega. I suppose you can call it Omega in the Quantum Vacuum. Whatever causes Omega in the Quantum Vacuum, I suppose maybe called an Axion. However, as such, the only thing that would be missing is Oscillation due to Omega in the Quantum Vacuum. Now if anyone wants to mention that it's now named, I can mention yea. However, it's still repeated, and in this case, it's repeated just because it is Omega (reactance/Theta) in the Quantum Vacuum.

Maybe I am wrong to be so bold and suggest that naming something is not more important than finding it. Here we are though, pretending that naming something is more important than finding it.

I think I am angry that Reactance and Inductor aren't recognized as words in Computer Application Dictionaries. I am happy with everything else.

Since the subject is mostly about seeing through things in some of the demonstrations in the video, I have to wonder, whatever happened to "Muons"? I thought that was their thing. Now it's "Axions".

snippet.textDisplay: Also, here’s an idea explaining dark matter and dark energy. If matter is attracted to anti matter and anti matter is repelled from matter and anti matter is attracted to anti matter, then anti matter would be pushed out and away from our tangible matter parts of the universe and clump into anti matter parts of the universe. This would occur during the creation of virtual particle pairs. This would pull our matter part of the universe in every direction, stretching the universe as we know it. snippet.textDisplay:
Not really part of this video, but a shower thought I had.

Regarding merging singularities. A singularity at the center off a black hole should be a one dimensional point. Making it impossible for two to ever merge. Two points can only ever approach each other but never reach each other. Which makes it impossible for them to merge, none the less we observe black holes merge and act as if there is one singularity on the inside.
So here is my thought, what if the plank length takes part in making it so? So far the plank length seems to be a real thing. The smallest distance in the universe in which stuff like time and space still has meaning. What if the universe, regarding two approaching singularities, regards them as one (or they do merge or something along those lines) the moment the distance between the two singularities falls below the plank length?
